W. POOSER v. JACKSON COUNTY, a political sub-division of the State of Florida. 33 So. (2nd) 602 January 20, 1948

January Term, 1948

Division B W. Pooser, in Proper Person, for appellant. Clyde Mayhall, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

Affirmed on authority of Kirkland v. State, 86 Fla. 64, 97 So. 502 (headnotes 9 and 10); County of Okeechobee, et al. v. Florida National Bank of Jacksonville, 112 Fla. 309, 150 So. 124 (4th headnote).

So ordered.

THOMAS, C. J., BUFORD, ADAMS and BARNS, JJ., concur.
